President Muhammadu Buhari has re-christened the Abuja National Stadium as ‘Moshood Abiola Stadium’ in the honour of the deceased as the globally acclaimed winner of the ingloriously annulled June 12, 1993 election. The President made this declaration during the Democracy Day speech at the Eagles Square this afternoon. The event rounded off at 12:30pm. Inuwa Congratulates Lawan, Gbajabiamila, Says They Are Loyal Party Men